author: @dcrespin
text: One input layer, one output layer and one hidden layer are always sufficient.   Moreover the number of processing units in each of the layers as well as the numerical values of the weights can be calculated directly from the training vectors.  No backpropagation is needed.  More details available in this video:  NNB Deep Learning Without Backpropagation In the video description there is a link to download the free Demo software.  Regards, Daniel Crespin
